    "comment_id" : 111737572,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "Generally avoid assuming how a broken cast would work.  Certainly C compilers can do weird things.  Better to test against max int and min int, or to mask off the bottom 32 bits.  Not checking for integer overflow is an idiocy Java inherited from C.  It costs nothing using hardware traps.  More sophisticated languages like Visual Basic do check by default, and that has saved me on a few occasions."
  } ],
